==English==
===Etymology===
Middle English [[flod]], from Old English [[flod|flód]], from common Germanic ''*flōduz'', from Proto-Indo-European ''*plō-tu-'', derived from ''*pleu-'' "to flow". Near cognates include German [[Flut]] and Gothic [[𐍆𐌻𐍉𐌳𐌿𐍃]] (flōdus).  

